er florets in mixing bowl and chop <strong><b>15 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place remaining 400 g cauliflower florets in mixing bowl and chop <strong><b>15 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>."},{"content":"Add reserved chopped cauliflower, 15 g olive oil, milk, 1 tsp salt and ground pepper then cook <strong><b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b><\/strong>."},{"content":"Carefully remove the baked garlic bulb from the oven and squeeze it to extract the baked garlic cloves. Add baked garlic cloves to mixing bowl and blend <strong><b>1 min 30 sec\/speed 7<b><\/strong>. Serve chicken breasts with garlic-cauliflower purée, garnished with fresh thyme leaves."}],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","50m","4 portions"]}